cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper focuses on enabling large-scale energy-efficient IoT connectivity through self-coordination and learning from past communications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses low-complexity distributed learning approaches, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic geometry, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed solution, which could also place it in cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
